Those who give up freedom for security deserve neither
Safety and security are paramount on Maslow hierarchy of needs but your freedoms or lack their of directly impact that sense of security.
"Safety" is often achieved through government control. Big government will always cause the lack of safety and totalitarianism. True safety can only be achieved through true freedom.
Freedom. Benjamin Franklin said that he who sacrifices freedom for security deserves neither.
Freedom. When security is provided solely by the government at it's discretion, you are in no way safe.
"He who would trade liberty for some temporary security, deserves neither liberty nor security." -Benjamin Franklin
Freedom, by far
Someone’s freedom always infringes upon someone’s safety and someone’s safety always infringes upon someone’s freedom. It’s a perspective thing.
You can’t be safe if you’re not free
Freedom as our founding fathers intended
Safety is more important
I’d rather freedom with uncertain danger than “safety” with no sense of independence.
Freedom. You want security, you go to prison🤷‍♀️
